I Cabrius, call upon those of virtue to join me in a Valorous quest, one which promises to be rich in Sacrifice and Humility.
Decades ago, Lord British in his wisdom founded eight settlements, each dedicated to one of the Virtues. We Britannitans have lived up to lord's expectations, for the towns of Britain, Jhelom, Minoc, Moonglow, Skara Brae, Trinsic, and Yew have flourished to the present day.
 
I believe the time has come to found one further town, where all Eight Virtues are bound together into a unified whole. In order to people this new community, I call upon the most faithful among our citizenry to come forward in this cause - fighters and mages first, and later craftsmen and even children. 
 
And where shall this new town be located? This has been a matter of long discussion. At first it had been thought to place this colony in a setting conducive to its goals - A pleasant woodlands, adjacent to a placid lake, or even at the peak of a lofty mountain. However, I have since realized that the usefulness to all of Britannia should this Center of Virtue be situated
in such a place as to seal off a gate that has been in the past been used by Evil forces to trouble us - on the Isle of the Avatar, directly in the Great Stygian Abyss itself!
