#279
On the Battlements~
From this point on the western battlements you have a wonderful view of
the craggy peaks of the mountains that make up the Serpent's Spine.  The
range which spreads from the edge of Skara Brae to the High Steppes has been
a natural defense of Britain since the Third Age of Darkness, and have given
the native Britannians a sense of stability in their often chaotic world. 
However, the mountains are also home to several forms of hardy monster which
fortunately have learned not to approach the city, but have been known to
carry off an errant sheep or two, much to the farmers' dismay.  The
battlements continue to the south, and lead to a tower to the north.  A
small staircase to the east allows access to the flat roof of the castle.  
