Northwest Tower~
The northwest tower of Britannia Castle is little more than a glorified
storage chamber.  Through the barred door to the west, you can see several
sacks of grain and flour, and many barrels of preserved stock.  The sturdy
iron door seems quite impervious to attack, and the formidable lock
discourages would be thieves.  Two arches to the south and west provide
access to the battlements, allowing the Knight Watchmen to complete their
rounds.  
