#294
On the Battlements~
From your vantage point atop the battlements, you can see the bulk of
the city of Britain sprawled before you, stretching towards the horizon.  In
the distance, past the Town Hall and the trailing buildings, you can see the
beautiful blue sea that dips into Britanny Bay.  The merchant houses cluster
around the waterfront area, and several open air markets cluster in this
region.  The galleons and skiffs that ferry passengers back and forth move
in lazy course across the water, their beautiful sails catching the gentle
leeward wind off of the Serpents Spine.  The battlements continue to the
west, and lead to the guard tower to the east.  
