#295
Roof of the Castle~
The flat roof of the castle has traditionally been used as a ceremonial
tournament yard, where skilled duellists can spar in single combat.  It is
not a common practice, as most prefer to keep their duels in private, though
for matters of honor it is not uncommon for one or both of the combatants to
request the rooftop be the battlegrounds.  The battlements surround the
area, providing a natural raised area for the onlookers to watch from mush
to the watchmen's dismay.  This practice is tolerated however, especially in
the face of a particularly good match.  The roof continues to the north, and
stairs up to the battlements lie to the west and south.  
